programme.title: Navy Seals - Enemy Territory
programme.desc: From Al Qaeda to ISIS, from Iran to Afghanistan and from 9/11 to today, the secretive world of the Navy Seals remains on the front lines fighting the war on terror.

programme.title: Forged In Fire S5E16
programme.desc: Four bladesmiths must forge a blade from a bicycle; the final two must recreate an ancient, mysterious weapon called wind and fire wheels.

programme.title: Forged In Fire S7E1
programme.desc: In this special kung fu competition, four bladesmiths square off in the Forged in Fire dojo where they must make a matching set of three kunai throwing knives.

programme.title: Kings Of Pain E5
programme.desc: A dangerous underwater hunt for the deadly scorpion fish in the Baja California ocean leads to a toxic sting that puts Adam in danger, while the toe biter results in the weirdest pain profile yet.

programme.title: Monster Motor Challenge S2E5
programme.desc: It's the classic American rivalry: Chevy versus Ford. Drivers show off their power on the Slag Heap, and strategy separates winners and losers in the Cliff Plunge.

programme.title: The Pickers S12E16
programme.desc: Mike and Frank make good on a promise to restore a '1935 Auburn and take the original owners for a ride.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E7
programme.sub-title: The Search For Intelligent Life On Earth
programme.desc: A revelation of the hidden underground network that is a collaboration of four kingdoms of life, and a true first contact story between humans and beings who communicate in a symbolic language and have maintained a representative democracy for many tens of millions of years.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E8
programme.desc: The mysterious untold story of the scientist who figured out how to go the Moon while fighting for his life in a WWI trench. He wrote a letter to fifty years in the future. It made the Apollo Mission possible. And the saga of the twenty-year long odyssey of a robotic explorer ordered to commit suicide on another world.

programme.title: Supercar Megabuild S1E9
programme.desc: Ralph and Ranen are tasked with fulfilling Afzal Kahn's dream of producing one of the fastest road cars in the world. Kahn challenges them to engineer a car to beat his Bugatti Veyron in a straight quarter mile race. Their answer is a Nissan GTR with a specialist Japanese ECU hack. In three weeks they must overhaul the GTR and take it to Santa Pod Raceway for a supercar showdown.

programme.title: Is It Real? (30 Mins) E13
programme.desc: Following the reports of mutilated farm animals in Puerto Rico, eyewitnesses began coming forward to describe the predator. Said to have glowing red eyes, the face of a gargoyle and the wings of a vampire bat, the culprit was named El Chupacabras, “The Goat Sucker,” by the press. Quickly, the creature made the leap to parts of the U.S. and Latin America.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E2
programme.sub-title: Brie Larson In The Pearl Islands
programme.desc: Captain Marvel herself, Brie Larson accompanies Bear on a jungle adventure across a remote island in the Gulf of Panama. A 48-hour getaway from Hollywood is what this Oscar winner needs, but there's no such thing as a relaxing vacation with Bear Grylls! Their journey starts by jumping out of a helicopter into the ocean. From there, it's a perilous trek through a crocodile-filled mangrove swamp that turns into a dangerous maze as the tide rises. It'll take Bear's bush craft skills and Brie's super powers to complete this adventure!

programme.title: Inside Incredible Machines E2
programme.desc: Coal powered the birth of modern America and smokestacks dotted the landscape. As we turn to natural gas and renewables, engineer Chad Zdenek gets deep inside the workings of one of the nation's behemoth coal power stations in North Carolina before it's taken apart and consigned to history forever.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E5
programme.desc: Jordan heads to Providence, Rhode Island a small town bursting with late night eating opportunities. He starts off in College Hill at Durk's BBQ, the city's only Texas BBQ joint. Jordan bites into succulent brisket nachos sure to satisfy any late night appetite, and he gets a sweet surprise with Durk's tangy lemon chess pie.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E6
programme.desc: Jordan hits up Portland, Maine, a tiny New England town with a tremendous amount to offer late night. He starts off his night at Nosh, a late night hangout known for supersized sandwiches and over the top snack food. First up is a juicy burger made with four kinds of meat served on a mac and cheese bun. He tops that off with something from the 'lighter side' -- gooey, golden Polenta Cheese Fries.

programme.title: Science Of Stupid S6E13
programme.desc: In this episode we learn all about Icebergs, the many ways to hurt yourself jumping off a pier, and what to watch out for the next time you are biking over a teeter totter.

programme.title: Science Of Stupid S6E14
programme.desc: In this engineering special we discover the secrets behind explosive demolitions, exactly how dams work, and what you need to look out for when operating a ladder.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S19E9
programme.desc: LAM Mozambique Airlines Flight 470 is headed for Luanda, Angola, when it disappears from radar. Rangers in a remote Namibian park eventually discover the wreckage, and NTSB investigators join a local team for their largest-ever case. The wreckage provides the first major clue, and after ruling out a host of possible causes, investigators are left with an chilling conclusion.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E5
programme.desc: A voyage of discovery through the evolution of consciousness with stops in ancient Greece, a visit to the largest life form on Earth, into the poignant dream of an abandoned orphan that opened the way to our understanding of the architecture of thought and beyond to a vision of a galactic network of thought.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E6
programme.sub-title: The Man Of A Trillion Worlds
programme.desc: A child lies on the rug of a tenement dreaming of interstellar adventures. At the dawn of the space age, a young Carl Sagan's career is forged in the clash of his mentors, two scientific titans. Sagan goes on realize his childhood dreams, to carry their research forward and communicate its significance to the whole world.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E7
programme.sub-title: Joel Mchale In Arizona Slot Canyons
programme.desc: The often clever, always snarky actor and comedian Joel McHale joins Bear Grylls in the Arizona desert for an adventure unlike any other. They set out to traverse a massive slot canyon in hopes of surviving the wild, but first they have to survive one another! Huge cliffs, nasty food, and unorthodox survival strategies abound in this hilarious misadventure!

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E7
programme.desc: Jordan is headed to St. Louis. Known as the gateway to the west, this city is a gateway to a wide variety of culinary delights. Jordan kicks off his journey at a restaurant close to his own heart. Guerilla Street Foods serves up Filipino cuisine with a mid-west riff. Pork served street style with calamansi sauce and a poached egg, and fried chicken that finds the perfect blend of sweet, salty and tangy.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E8
programme.desc: Jordan's journey takes a turn full south with a trip to Music City. While Nashville may be best known for its music, it's next known for its mouthwatering cuisine. Jordan starts off his journey through this southern jewel at the Butcher and Bee, where globally inspired share plates bring joy to customers at all hours of the night.

programme.title: Inside Incredible Machines E3
programme.desc: Engineer Chad Zdenek joins a salvage team to tear apart the world's biggest hovercraft and reveal the engineering innovations that made it a legend of its time. In San Diego, he takes controls of the US Navy hovercraft fighting wars and saving lives around the world.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E7
programme.sub-title: The Search For Intelligent Life On Earth
programme.desc: A revelation of the hidden underground network that is a collaboration of four kingdoms of life, and a true first contact story between humans and beings who communicate in a symbolic language and have maintained a representative democracy for many tens of millions of years.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S19E10
programme.desc: Taking off during a major storm, a brand-new 737 falls from the sky over West Africa, and an international group of investigators soon descends on Cameroon. Submerged in mud and water, Kenya Airlines Flight 507 crashed into a mangrove swamp, killing everyone on board. And while investigators ultimately pinpoint one fatal mistake that triggered the tragedy, they also uncover a lethal cascade of issues that sent the passenger jet spiralling toward the ground.

programme.title: Car SOS S5E1
programme.desc: Car lover Chris has had his beloved, Ferrari engined, 1971 Fiat Dino coupe for nearly 25 years. The former engine mechanic had to put the restoration on hold when he was diagnosed with a rare type of cancer. Now it's up to Tim and Fuzz to get this rusting Dino back to its best. Tim takes a drive in one of the most beautiful cars in the world and Fuzz gets his hands on a Ferrari racing engine for the very first time.

programme.title: China Relics Decoded E2
programme.desc: China is the world's longest continuous civilization, but as the nation modernizes, there's a new thirst to rediscover its roots. Historian Sam Willis investigates the importance of the family to Chinese civilization and how it became the building block of Chinese society, shaping the nation from past to present.

programme.title: Explorer S3E13
programme.desc: Phil Keoghan journeys to North Carolina to see the science behind Nascar racing. Jago Cooper explores a chilling new discovery of human sacrifice. Francesca Fiorentini investigates what DNA tests actually tell you. Tim Samuels reveals a new probiotic made from the human gut.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E3
programme.sub-title: Zachary Quinto In The Panama Jungle
programme.desc: Bear Grylls and actor Zachary Quinto race the clock to traverse a dense Panamanian jungle before an impending storm makes landfall. Their adventure begins with a helicopter ride, but once dropped off deep in the brush, they must rely on a primitive navigation technique to help them reach their extraction point- but it won't be easy! From massive cliffs and steep ravines to an underground river cave and an old crashed plane, there are obstacles at every turn!

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E2
programme.desc: Let's take a rare look inside the Corvette Mega Factory which produces the ZR1 – a genuine American supercar. It's the fastest, most powerful, and most expensive Corvette ever built and it can compete against the best that Europe has to offer.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S1E3
programme.desc: Watch as a sacred mega kitchen gears up to feed over 100,000 devotees in a single day for the annual festival of Lakshadeepotsava in the temple town of Dharmasthala.

programme.title: The Happenings E1
programme.desc: Barry and Stuart arrive in the quiet town of Stamford in England. Their aim is to make the residents believe aliens have arrived. To convince the public that extraterrestrials have been watching them for years, they go undercover as filmmakers and paranormal researchers, and plan an alien abduction and work to convince residents that the extraterrestrials brainwashed their animals.

programme.title: Dictators Rulebook E4
programme.desc: An exploration of the methods and tactics of Generalissimo Francisco Franco, who controlled Spain with absolute power for four decades. Employing violence and terror learned in colonial warfare, Franco led the 1936 military coup that overthrew the legitimately elected government and went on to rule the nation as his personal fiefdom until his death in 1975. The mass graves of his victims are being exhumed to this day.

programme.title: Mega Air E8
programme.desc: Mega Air gets up close to the most bizarre air freighter on the planet, the bulbous Airbus Beluga, a flying whale that swallows entire aircraft wings. We chart the misfortunes of a wealthy, American classic car enthusiast, airfreighting one of the earliest cars ever built to a famous UK car rally; and, to much fanfare, global mega movers, UPS take delivery of a brand-new Boeing 747-8, the largest freighter made in the US.

programme.title: Hidden Gems Of Turkey E3
programme.desc: National Geographic's Digital Nomad Andrew Evans completes his journey across Turkey in search of hidden gems by crossing the Bosphorus to the European side of Istanbul. Here, he immerses himself in the city's multicultural heritage, exploring how the city's unique location and complex history have shaped Istanbul today. Getting lost in its streets, he brings us a colourful picture of the city today.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E8
programme.sub-title: Channing Tatum In The Mountains Of Norway
programme.desc: It's been five years since Channing Tatum first appeared on Running Wild, and he's back for more- this time in the wilds of Norway! Their journey kicks off by skydiving into brutal terrain where giant boulder fields and towering cliffs stand in the way of extraction. During their seven-mile trek, Bear tests Channing to see how far he's come as a survivor - from foraging for food to Navy SEAL style cold-water emersion training. Channing even learns the ancient art of trout tickling!

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S1E4
programme.desc: In order to feed passengers 35,000 feet up in the air, there's an army of chefs on the ground in the mega flight kitchens of TajSATS Delhi dishing up over 22,000 meals a day - from Economy to First Class!

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E9
programme.desc: What makes a car worth a million Euros? The answer for Horacio Pagani is a supercar that perfectly blends art and engineering, that has unsurpassed power, performance and luxury, the finest possible raw materials and in which every single one of its 4700 components will be recognized as a work of art. This film tells the story of Pagani's successor to his world famous Zonda.

programme.title: 100%: Planes
programme.desc: 100% Planes tells amazing aviation stories from around the world, featuring aircrafts from the smallest microlight to the biggest cargo plane, and everything in between. Circumnavigate the globe, travel to the most beautiful and exotic locations, and hear the stories of pilots flying the most interesting and unusual planes.

programme.title: The Story Of God With Morgan Freeman S3E1
programme.desc: Morgan Freeman delves into why many religious believers desire to see God in human form - and how that strengthens their faith. From a living Kumari Goddess in the mountains of Nepal, to the Crown of Thorns many Christians believe was worn by Jesus during the crucifixion, Morgan will discover that these tangible connections help people make sense of the divine.

programme.title: Dictators Rulebook E5
programme.desc: A study of the methods used by Manuel Noriega to rise from poverty to become dictator of Panama for six tumultuous years in the 1980s. As Chief of Intelligence he was the most feared man in Panama. He developed connections inside and outside the country that made him rich, powerful, and a key ally of the US in the region, while also working for Fidel Castro and the Medellin drug cartel, among others.

programme.title: Nazi World War Weird E2
programme.desc: 10 May 1940, thanks to the blitzkrieg the Nazis capture Belgium's most impregnable fortress, Fort Eben Emael, in less than 15 minutes. Dr. Sam Willis and Robert Joe investigate the victory and discover that a performance enhancing drug called Pervitin, an earlier version crystal meth, might have been fueling the Wehrmacht in their march over Europe.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E4
programme.desc: Actress, supermodel, and social media influencer Cara Delevingne realizes a long-held dream of accompanying Bear Grylls on an adventure. Sweeping Cara off her scooter and onto a helicopter, the two ascend into the mountains of Sardinia. At nearly a mile high in elevation, Bear shows Cara how to brave several heart-stopping obstacles including pulling herself across a horizontal line suspended 200 feet in the air and a dangerous waterfall rappel.

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures: America's War E2
programme.desc: September 1944. The Japanese have suffered catastrophic defeats across the Pacific. Wasting men in a futile attempt to expel the enemy at the beach is no longer viable if they are to protect the Home Islands. On Peleliu the Japanese build an island-wide defensive megastructure that creates a killing zone unprecedented in the Pacific. What unfolds is one of the most brutal battles of World War Two. Americans are killed in their thousands.

programme.title: Gok's Chinese Takeaway E2
programme.desc: Gok's journey begins with Elizabeth Chong, a local food guru and an author who traces back to her grandfather in the 1850s for family recipes. She teaches Gok the frugal dishes like Steamed Egg Custard and Lap Yook Potatoes. Inspired by local gastronomy, Gok returns to his own kitchen and creates an Aussie-Asian feast as a tribute to this city.

programme.title: Nazi World War Weird E3
programme.desc: As the chaos of World War II engulfs Italy, a British officer discovers a 900 year old castle near the front line containing a vast collection of priceless artworks by some of Italy's greatest Renaissance masters. Hosts Dr. Sam Willis and Robert Joe are on site at Montegufoni Castle to get to the bottom of the tale.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S12E10
programme.desc: Texan cousins Paris and Marlon always fancied themselves as entrepreneurs. When Paris' dad offers them the opportunity to run a car wash in Lima, Peru, they jump at the chance. But Peru has a dark side and the boys have no idea their ambitions to make money are leading them into grave personal danger. Ahead of them lies incarceration, attempted murder and the ultimate family betrayal.

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E10
programme.desc: In this story of Hitler's vision to conquer the world using his high-tech battleships, Drain the Oceans reveals the rise and fall of the Third Reich's deadly fleet.

programme.title: Petra: Secrets Of The Ancient Builders
programme.desc: In the heart of the Jordanian desert, the ancient city of Petra is full of mysteries. How was this architectural prowess achieved more than 2,000 years ago?

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E9
programme.desc: On-Air radio personality Bobby Bones joins Bear Grylls for the adventure of a lifetime in a massive Norwegian Fjord! A helicopter ride into the mountains is where their journey begins but from there, danger lurks at every turn - from giant rock domes and deadly bogs to raging rivers with currents strong enough to move cars. On top of that, the only way to reach their extraction is a 300-foot waterfall rappel that leaves even Bobby speechless!

programme.title: Gok's Chinese Takeaway E3
programme.desc: Gok Wan explores fusion food in Malaysia through a group of Chinese immigrants known as the Peranakans. His journey begins in the capital of Malaysia, Kuala Lumpur, where he learns the art of making Roti Jala, a Malay-style pancake made from a batter of coconut milk and turmeric. Gok's journey continues in producing his own Belachan, a shrimp sauce used in a fish curry.

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures: America's War E3
programme.desc: This is the story of Japan's final months of world war two. When America threatens to invade, the Japanese turn their country into a fortress and unleash a terrifying new weapon, suicide bombers. With surrender not an option, the Japanese prepare for the ultimate showdown on home soil. They plan to mobilise the entire country. Civilians must be ready to fight in hand-to-hand combat.

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E11
programme.desc: Drain the Oceans solves one of the world's great mysteries - the identity of the Loch Ness Monster. Comparisons with the deepest lake on Earth - Lake Baikal in Russian Siberia, combined with military-grade scanning technology and a sonar curtain drawn across its entire surface - the plug is pulled on Scotland's famous loch. As the waters drain away, much more than a monster is revealed.

programme.title: Lawless Island Alaska Compilations S2E1
programme.desc: Long-time resident of Lawless Island, Gary Muelberger has seen it all. A fisherman. A trapper. His roots to Lawless Island are deep and his knowledge of how to subsistence live unmatched.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S8E1
programme.desc: Susan Haglof moves to Egypt with her husband and adopts a newborn, named Marko. However Marko doesn't come with any papers and there is no proof that Susan is his adoptive mother. Hence she makes the decision to buy a birth certificate with her and her husband's name on it. Less than a year later, Susan is charged and facing jail time, however the worst is she may never see Marko again.

programme.title: United Plates Of America E2
programme.desc: California was once called Mexico before the United States purchased it. In San Diego we eat the real Mexican food from those who do it best. And we go on a beer tour and taste the best craft beers money can buy.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E1
programme.sub-title: What The Region Is Famous For
programme.desc: Chef and Restaurateur Peter Kuruvita begins a new culinary adventure in the extraordinary region of Margaret River; discovering a world of food, wine and colourful characters along the way.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E2
programme.desc: Peter continues his journey throughout Margaret River meeting extraordinary artisanal producers of the region and using their ingredients in a host of delicious dishes.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E53
programme.desc: Ben joins Brock Kerslake from Taste Walk Talk to do a food crawl around Launceston. In Brisbane, Ben and Joel cook up a classic comfort food, Banana Brulee. Back in the studio kitchen, Ben is joined by Tania Jago from Chef's Toolbox, to see which is better at making a Thai Green Chicken Curry, man or machine.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E54
programme.desc: Ben takes a trip to Clover Hill, an award-winning winery situated in the picturesque Launceston countryside. Here Ben cooks a delicious Prawn and Hot Sauce Omelette, before being joined by Adam Torpy, who will chat to Ben about pairing wines with food.

programme.title: Heathrow S5E1
programme.desc: Heathrow: Britain's Busiest Airport is busier than ever with drama from the get-go. Inside the terminal seasoned pro Demi dishes out deals for delayed passengers, and outside on the airfield, airside Ian is on the runway as it goes into lockdown, with a full-on armed police emergency.

programme.desc: 80% of all visitors to Britain arrive by air, and today's episode of Heathrow begins at 04:49 with the arrival of a 17 hour non-stop flight from Perth. Border Force pull over a Ghananian business man declaring 114 grand in cash, and there's love in the air, with a blind date at the romantic venue of T5 arrivals, and the end of an era on the airfield for Chief Trainer Simon.

programme.title: Cruise Ship Diaries S1E4
programme.desc: Nomadi, a famous band, is set to perform a rock concert in the theatre of the Costa Serena. Security has to be beefed up to handle difficult fans and paparazzi. But the day has not started out well as the ship arrives in Venice late due the thick mist, and there is less time to prepare before the next boarding of the German passengers and the rock stars.

programme.title: Fearless Chef E9
programme.desc: The Fearless Chef endures death-defying and claustrophobic conditions when he visits the coastal region of southwest Sri Lanka on the hunt for fresh tiger prawns and a naturally fermented palm wine.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E10
programme.desc: Let's travel to the cloudy forests of Chiapas near the border with Guatemala where Peter explores a state with the highest indigenous population in Mexico and with it, some of the most interesting food yet.

programme.title: Around The World In 80 Dishes E1
programme.desc: Manu Feildel is a household name in Australia as co-host of the smash-hit My Kitchen Rules, as well as being an award-winning chef and author. programme.desc: Ben heads to the Mersey Bluff, his local beach on the North West of Tasmania and cooks a vegetarian bruschetta. At The University of Queensland, Ben and Joel are going to create a tuna dish. In the studio, Ben creates a Mexican styles lasagna.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E64
programme.desc: Ben creates a chicken and pineapple tostada in the gardens at his home. At The University of Queensland Ben uses a pressure cooker to create a Mexican soup, with the help of Andrew Stevenson to explain why a pressure cooker speeds up the cook time of a recipe. programme.title: Korean Soul Food
programme.desc: With a sound reputation of being healthy, balanced and flavorsome, Korean food has drawn global attention and attracted people around the world to visit the bustling capital city, Seoul. In the company of actress Eun-Hye Park, we'll be revealing the taste and history of a variety of popular Korean dishes, including samgyetang and bibimbap, as well as investigating their healthy cooking principal.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E9
programme.desc: Sara strolls down memory lane and ranks her top five moments in Australia. From Melbourne, Darwin to Broome and Victoria, she prepares unforgettable delicacies like lamp chop and octopus bashing. Also, she savors unique cuisines like pizza made by alfresco oven. Other than cooking, Sara spends time with a group of kangaroos feeding on grass and also witnesses an alligator hunting for food.

programme.title: San Diego: More To Explore E1
programme.desc: Seventy miles of coastline, near perfect weather, and an exciting urban center, there's always an adventure to be had in California's first city. With an endless bucket list of opportunities, it'd be hard to find a better vacation destination. Soar through the skies, uncover hidden speakeasies, and step aboard a 16th century ship- discover what makes San Diego a city of Adventure.

programme.title: John Torode's Malaysian Adventure E10
programme.desc: John arrives on the beautiful Island of Langkawi where he receives a step-by-step guide on making the famous Malaysian dish, duck rendang. He also makes his way to one of the most exclusive hotels on the island and helps chef Rihizul Othman cook up a tantalizing dish of grouper bakar samba, against a sublime backdrop of the talcum-powder beach of Datai Bay.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E16
programme.desc: A 700-year-old village of the Angami Nagas is a perfect example of a close-knit community. Pablo gets a glimpse of their community culture visiting a community house followed by a community kitchen where he devours on some exotic Naga food. What surprised Pablo the most about this tribe was their transformation from fierce headhunters to farmers.

programme.title: Fearless Chef E10
programme.desc: The Fearless Chef, Kiran Jethwa, visits the legendary headhunters of Borneo, the Iban tribe, to face a grueling hunt through thick jungle in search of wild boar, edible frogs and palm hearts.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E55
programme.desc: Ben ventures back to the beautiful Tarkine Rainforest in Tasmania's far North-West, where he cooks a simple dessert, Charred Stonefruit with Ginger. Back at The University of Queensland, Ben is joined by Dr. Joel Gilmore. Here they discuss a very controversial topic - why some people don't like coriander and the science behind it.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E56
programme.desc: Ben makes the most of a beautiful sunny day to make a Cherry, Chocolate and Salted Caramel dessert in his own backyard. Then Ben heads back to The University of Queensland and meets up with Dr. Joel Gilmore, where they cook Mexican hotdogs that are inspired by Ben's pet dogs.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted S1E1
programme.desc: High in Peru's Sacred Valley of the Incas, Chef Ramsay is a man on a mission, travelling by motorbike to unlock the secrets of high altitude cuisine.

programme.desc: Champion spear fisher Kimi Werner visits a woman living a largely subsistence way of life and learns about her lifestyle. She's in pursuit of a deep truth about what it means to live more simply, more freely, and with a closer connection to nature.

programme.title: Get Lost In Korea
programme.desc: A photographer Greg Goodman teams up with Jesse Day, a Canadian rapper living in Seoul to discover the gems of Korea. They kick off their journey in Seoul to experience the night life. Then, they head to Shinan to dig mud for octopus and swallow it alive. After the fresh cuisine, they undergo rigorous training of Zen martial arts with the monks in Andong. It's a journey of humor and friendship!

programme.title: John Torode's Asia E1
programme.desc: Today's Asian adventure takes John Torode to Mumbai on the west coast of India. He begins his culinary exploration with a dusky guided tour of the street food served on Chowpatty Beach. Inspired by his cooking lessons and laden with produce from a visit to a local market, John undertakes a brand new dish of his own, Mango Samosas with a yogurt and mint dip. But are they any good?

programme.title: San Diego: More To Explore E2
programme.desc: Explore San Diego's many diverse offerings - from laid-back coastal towns to lively urban centers. Brimming with vibrant personalities and unique landscapes, San Diego has something for everyone.

programme.title: Hakka Renaissance E1
programme.desc: Historian anthropologist Julian Davison is teaming up with Natalie Pickles, host and model of British and Taiwanese descent. It's a journey of a lifetime for the unlikely duo as they traverse across Taiwan's north-western hinterlands, along a 150 km stretch of highway known as the Romantic Route 3. Meeting with local historian Chen Ban, they trace the footsteps of Hakka pioneers along a series of mountain trails that formed the backbone of their livelihood, transporting commodities and goods. Travelling further south, they get their hands dirty and learn how camphor, one of Taiwan's treasures is traditionally extracted. The duo also learn more about a tea that was created by the Hakka, that embodies the very spirit of what it means to be part of a ethnicity that were once outcasts.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E17
programme.desc: Mokukchung is the cultural capital for the Ao Nagas. Aos is one of the major Naga tribes of Nagaland. As Pablo visits Mokokchung, he gets to witness the diversity of Nagas at the Moatsumung Festival. A colorful, spirited festival that brings together the entire Naga Community.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E1
programme.desc: Fish of the Day host Clarke Gayford joins Joe and Laura on ‘Big Blue' a 44ft Sailing Catamaran. Along the way he will jet boat up a river to a remote village, dive with huge bull sharks and track down local chef Lance Seeto to unlock an ancient local recipe.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E2
programme.desc: Fish of the Day host Clarke Gayford shows off his hometown of Gisborne. This includes hand feeding friendly wild stingrays and venturing out to his favourite fishing and diving spots trying to track down an unusual fish called a Pink Maomao. Along the way they encounter huge schools of Kingfish and a couple of friendly sharks.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E65
programme.desc: In the final episode Ben heads back down to his local, the Mersey Bluff Beach, here he creates a simple dish, using some wood roasted salmon. He checks out the Huon Salmon hatchery and has a chat with David Mitchell about their processes. At The University of Queensland Ben is joined by Professor Neena Mitter, who is aiming to change the game of growing avocados, together they make an avocado chutney full of flavour.

programme.desc: Adventurer Ellis Emmett sets sail for the islands of Fiji, where he comes face to face with bull sharks, partakes in ancient Fijian fire walking rituals, and anchors in the remote Lau Islands, a beautiful place with a violent past.

programme.title: Somewhere In China E5
programme.desc: Peter and Jeff Hutchins visit with the Buddhist monks of China. Buddhism was once the dominant religion, and the brothers will explore the traditions of the monks, from the yellow hat Tibetans to the rainforest temples of the Dai Buddhists. Despite the many changes in the country, these traditions are still thriving.

programme.title: Eat: The Story Of Food E5
programme.desc: Throughout history, mankind has been on a mad-dash to satisfy our prodigious sweet tooth and consume vital energy. Along the way sugar helped build empires and even fueled the Industrial Revolution. From the time sugarcane was first refined in India, to our newest high-tech candy factories, we've been developing newer and better delivery systems for the taste we can't live without.

programme.title: Don't Tell My Mother S3E9
programme.desc: Diego explores where past and present collide in the biggest city in the world, Tokyo. Japan is one of the most technologically-advanced places on the planet, and in the richest city in Asia, the line between reality and fiction seems thin. From the wild to the traditional, the classic to the outlandish, discover Tokyo like you've never seen it before.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E10
programme.desc: Let's travel to the cloudy forests of Chiapas near the border with Guatemala where Peter explores a state with the highest indigenous population in Mexico and with it, some of the most interesting food yet.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E2
programme.desc: Formerly a colony of Portugal, Goa still has a large Portuguese population, and nowhere is their influence more evident than in the local cuisine. David is on a mission to discover Goa's unique blend of Portuguese and Indian cultures, one dish at a time. He also learns about the Toddy Vinegar that gives many dishes their signature Goan touch.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E3
programme.desc: David heads out on a crab fishing expedition with some local fishermen in a nearby river. Afterwards, he meets up with an internationally-renowned chef Cyrus Todiwala, who takes him to the local fish market to check out what is on offer. Later, David gets a chance to explore Goa's famous beach shack culture and ventures into Calamari, a renowned seafood restaurant, to flex his culinary muscles.

Here Ben meets with Adam Torpy, who tells us a bit about their new building and how it reflects the surrounding landscape. Ben then heads to The University of Queensland where he meets up with Dr. Joel Gilmore. Here Ben teaches us how to create his Never Fail Meringue dessert.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E58
programme.desc: Ben heads down to his local beach, the Mersey Bluff to create his version of the Prawn Cocktail. Up at The University of Queensland, Ben recreates the pumpkin soup from his first book, Mexican Craving. In the studio Ben makes a bite sized burger, the perfect canape dish.

programme.title: Somewhere In China E6
programme.desc: Peter and Jeff Hutchens visit the capital city, Beijing. They seek to compare the new with the old, and nowhere is this more stark than in Beijing. They meet with a local punk band, play table tennis with a member of the Communist Youth League, and travel to Inner Mongolia, where life has remained relatively unchanged for centuries.

programme.title: Eat: The Story Of Food E6
programme.desc: What we eat and how we eat today has changed so much that our great grandparents would hardly recognize it. We spend less of our time on food than ever before. How did this happen and what does it mean? Guilty Pleasures explores modern food and its uneasy relationship between convenience and quality.

programme.title: Island Hunter E1
programme.desc: The Island Hunter season starts off in the beautiful and highly popular tourism hotspot; Bali. The host, Liesel Hlista embarks on a mission to understand how the Balinese blend hospitality with luxury. And this is a journey that takes place on land, underwater and even in the air! A soothing journey that finds ultra luxurious healing centers such as Como Shambhala amidst the lush jungles of Ubud - to a hands on cooking stint at the Balinese fusion restaurant Mozaic, to checking out true African style Safaris in the heart of Bali. Helicopter rides over volcanos and reef-rescuing innovative dive resorts. This is an adventure true to the Island Hunter style.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E4
programme.desc: David visits the Savoi Plantations managed and run by the Shetye family. It is over 200 years old and covers 100-acres, where they grow all manners of Indian fruits including coconut and mango as well as almost every spice under the sun. David cooks, eats and spends time with the Shetye family to learn about organic farming and what it truly means to live off the land.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E5
programme.desc: Kollam is a beautiful old seaport city in Kerala known for its breathtaking backwaters so scenic that you would think you were on the set of a movie when floating down the calm rivers through the dense foliage. David explores life in this verdant region by digging for clams, taking a tour down the river aboard a floating restaurant, and cooking for guests at a local hotel.

programme.title: Confucius Was A Foodie S3E1
programme.desc: This episode sees Christine learning firsthand the very challenging ‘how to' of harvesting sea salt in Thailand's dramatically beautiful salt fields. Cushing visits the area's most unusual market that is regularly disrupted by the Maeklong Railway going right through it's center!

programme.title: Around The World In 80 Dishes E2
programme.desc: At his first stop after London, Manu arrives in Dubai where he has lined up some work in exchange for accommodations. Manu is keen on the culinary experience in Dubai so he sets off to the spice souk, fish markets, and a local pastry kitchen before having an experience of a lifetime in the desert, with food never far from the scene. Then it's onto India and a challenging train journey.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E9
programme.desc: In the 24 hour build special George Clarke takes on the 600 year old legend of the Ty Unnos; a piece of Welsh folklore that claims that if you can build a house with four walls, a roof and have a fire burning in your hearth in less than a day, then that house and the ground beneath it is yours.

programme.title: Shark Men S2E2
programme.desc: The Expedition Great White team is in strange waters, having to worry about the safety of the Great Whites they are catching as well as any nearby beach goers in the crowded waters of Southern California. They are after one of the smallest sharks they've seen, and so far this little fighter is throwing them off their game.

programme.title: Wild 24 S3E3
programme.desc: Life in the fabled Rocky Mountains is hard once winter sweeps through the mountain valleys as it is the season of the rut where big animals fight for mating rights. The fight turns bitter as the temperature drops and the cold sweeps in. Nonetheless, the animals face their enemies head-on as it is an inevitable fight for the next generation.

programme.title: Kingdom Of The White Wolf E2
programme.desc: As Winter approaches, the pack is running out of food and needs a fresh kill. White Scarf leads the pack in a successful hunt of a muskox calf, and ensures that the pups eat first. As the pack sleeps with full bellies, White Scarf limps away and doesn't return.

programme.title: Wild Cambodia
programme.desc: We take you to wild Cambodia, where the extreme monsoon weather systems have created one of the most unique ecosystems on the planet. This ancient land was once ruled by a great empire, yet life here is dictated by an unforgiving weather system, from a life-sucking dry season to wet season defined by floods, shaping an incredibly diverse wildlife that you should not miss.

programme.title: Shark Men S2E2

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E4
programme.desc: Simon and Sioux nearly get bitten catching and releasing mating Boomslangs. Teamwork is everything, but sometimes they split up to help all the snakes.

programme.title: Hostile Planet E3
programme.desc: Step inside the most frigid habitat known to Earth - the poles. Here, the planet's ultimate survivalists include whale-hunting polar bears, leopard-seal dodging penguins and a pack of Arctic wolves that bring down a pair of musk oxen. Polar species have evolved bodies and behaviours that help them combat the intense hostility of their habitats. But now, their world is changing so fast - literally breaking apart under their feet - and their resilience will be tested beyond the extreme.

programme.title: Hunt For The Giant Squid
programme.desc: Antarctica is the coldest place on Earth. It's too harsh for most life forms to survive on land. But underwater life is totally different. Using deep-sea submersibles equipped with state-of-the-art cameras, marine biologists set out to explore one of the world's most exotic places. The Southern Sea is home to bizarre and sometimes gigantic sea creatures. The scientist's journey takes us into a hostile and inaccessible world locked away under snow and ice to experience the magic spell of these ocean giants.

programme.title: World's Deadliest Compilations E2
programme.desc: The ocean is a predator's paradise. In waters bustling with life, creatures develop sophisticated skills and weaponry to survive and thrive. From coastal reef assassins to goliaths of the deep, these hunters deal out a one-way ticket to Davy Jones' locker.

programme.title: The Pack E2
programme.desc: A single African Hunting Dog is a tough, agile predator. A pack of them is a singular force of nature, able to take on prey many times their size and strength. Travel to Umfolozi Game Reserve in South Africa, and uncover how allegiances are built, strategies planned and teamwork developed, turning these canines into an elite hunting unit.

programme.title: Wild Sri Lanka E1
programme.desc: The seas surrounding Sri Lanka boasts an incredible array of habitats, all full of life. Sri Lanka's seas tell us much about how the island came to be – the vast, slow forces that underpin the extraordinary diversity of the island we see today. They also tell the story of Sri Lanka's complex climate and the ancient roots of many of the species that inhabit the island today.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E6
programme.desc: A huge black mamba hides under the kitchen sink, Simon rips apart a couch to find a spitter and climbs a tree to catch a highly-venomous vine snake.

programme.title: Hostile Planet E5
programme.desc: Delve beneath the surface of the largest habitat on Earth - our oceans - to uncover a world of extraordinary extremes from crushing depths to stormy coasts and vast blue deserts to crowded reefs. Oceans are dynamic environments where animals must adapt to life of constant change. Discover how seals fend off sharks; how turtles risk their lives to create their next generation; and how ingenious orca fight to survive in the face of ever-increasing competition.

programme.desc: The Expedition team takes a trip into the unfamiliar, cold, dark, and Jellyfish-infested waters near the Farallon Islands and Big Slur, California. In the murky waters of this protected marine sanctuary, they are facing some of the biggest sharks they have ever encountered, and things are not going to plan.

programme.title: Wild 24 S3E4
programme.desc: In the mystic river - the Nile, wildlife like hippos, crocodiles, lions, wolves, mole rats and lungfish pull out all stops to survive. When the river flows, the backdrop changes from mountain to rainforest; when the water retreats, the habitat turns from swamp to desert. No one can defy the forces of nature.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E3 !
programme.sub-title: There's A Snake In The Fridge
programme.desc: It's mamba season and these deadly snakes are simply everywhere! In this episode of Snake City, they're playing hard-to-get in trees, boxes and even a refrigerator as Simon risks his life to save them. There's also double-trouble when he realizes he's in a small, dark room with not one, but two highly-venomous Forest cobras!

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S5E4
programme.desc: This killer episode of Animal Fight Club reveals how some of the most dangerous fights in the animal kingdom are between the same species, whether for territory, bloodline or survival. It also shows the amazing escape techniques fighters use to escape death. Top wildlife film makers and user generated footage from around the world prove that from top predators to the smallest insects, life is a constant battle - and there can only be one winner.

programme.title: Climbing Redwood Giants: Life In The Sky
programme.desc: Climbing Redwood Giants- Life in the Sky tells the story of the worlds tallest living trees. Humboldt State Universitys Steve Sillett, the first researcher to explore the redwood canopy, is obsessed with monster redwoods. As Sillett investigates redwoods up in their towering crowns, National Geographic Photographer Jim Balog photographs every inch of these fascinating trees.

programme.title: Hostile Planet E4
programme.desc: The planet's hottest habitats - our deserts - are getting even hotter, drier and bigger, yet a host of remarkable animals still survive in the harshest conditions, including cunning hyenas, pint-sized meerkats and sand-dwelling spiders. Follow their lives through a single day in the desert to appreciate how they deal with the sun's formidable power as it grows stronger with every passing minute.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S1E1
programme.desc: Mat is beside himself with excitement at the possibility of creating fish tanks for the home plate backstop of the new Miami Marlins baseball stadium. However, Jose can't get back on track with his production schedule and an overlooked design flaw in the Marlins reefs could botch the delivery date. Will they be able to create tanks that will safely house the fish in the Marlin ballpark?

programme.title: World's Deadliest S2E3
programme.desc: Whether it's to hunt or to protect itself against predators, there are spine-chilling killing machines ready to mutate in surprising and amazing ways. From color changing to shape shifting, getting fierce, turning up the heat, fooling their prey or simply letting it fly, these animals will do anything it takes to survive on World's Deadliest: Transformers.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E5
programme.desc: Sioux comes face-to-face with a Green mamba, Simon is almost bitten by a Black mamba and they catch two bizarre snakes that don't belong in Durban!

programme.title: World's Deadliest (2019) E1
programme.desc: Carnivores are designed to kill so what happens when the deadliest go head to head? Meerkats fight in the deserts, a cuttlefish turns a reef into a warzone, a killer shrew wreaks havoc in the fields, baby alligators fight to survive the deadly swamp, Lions take on hyenas and tigers take on each other as carnivores battle each other to survive Nature's eternal war.

programme.title: Wild Indonesia (2015) E1
programme.desc: On Indonesias eastern frontier lies an ancient world forged by fire. Isolated for thousands of years it is a land of extremes where creatures have evolved beyond recognition. Each habitat harbours a unique mix of the bold and the bizarre as Papuas lost worlds support one of the richest and strangest concentrations of life on our planet.

programme.title: Wild Indonesia (2015) E2
programme.desc: Borneo is the worlds third largest island, and Sumatra is no dwarf in comparison. Both islands became cut off from the Asian mainland when sea levels rose at the end of the last ice age 12,000 years ago. Large animals became marooned, isolated from their mainland cousins. Over time, they have adapted and evolved to their new home developing an array of unique traits on each island. Today, these are the Islands of Monsters.

The crew can't do anything but wait for clarification from the authorities and the suspense and stress is taking its toll.

programme.title: Wild 24 S3E5
programme.desc: Alaska is a frost-bound place where bears, whales, salmon, orca, walruses and beavers are racing the seasons, trying to make the most out of the brief summer. They need to spend time every day to save food energy for a rainy day because the return of icy darkness will cut off their food supply and leave them to starve.

programme.title: Dr Oakley: Yukon Vet S6E8
programme.desc: Dr. Oakley participates in a race pitting human runners against reindeer, five muskox undergo pregnancy tests, and Daisy participates in a family reunion.

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S4E4
programme.desc: Here comes another 3 pairs of special friends you've never seen before: a wild fawn who is friends with a dog, an autistic four-year-old child who comes out of his shell with the help of his feathered friends (a flock of chickens), and a cat that's friends with a rat.

programme.desc: Get ready to brush feathers with the freakiest birds in the world as we take to the sky. Check out dancing manakins that do the moonwalk, shrikes impaling their prey before ripping it apart, and lyrebirds singing snazzy solos. Some of the freaks don't even need wings for takeoff - flying squirrels, flying snakes, and carps springing from the water to knock people out, will blow your mind.

programme.title: Wild Cambodia
programme.desc: We take you to wild Cambodia, where the extreme monsoon weather systems have created one of the most unique ecosystems on the planet. This ancient land was once ruled by a great empire, yet life here is dictated by an unforgiving weather system, from a life-sucking dry season to wet season defined by floods, shaping an incredibly diverse wildlife that you should not miss.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S1E5
programme.desc: Mat gets a call from a high-profile recording studio in Las Vegas with a tank that has aged prematurely and is due for a major aquatic overhaul. The studio caters to famed artists like Lady Gaga and Wayne Newton so the team's work will be seen by VIPs year round. Meanwhile, Francis is busy fact finding information on a nurse shark that needs to be relocated quickly.

programme.title: World's Deadliest S2E4
programme.desc: Welcome to the deadly world of the most armed and dangerous gangsters, assassins, and con artists of the animal kingdom. Be surrounded by a gang of flesh-eating fish taking down a river rat, a Bengal tiger showing how to get the job done alone, and a pack of killer whales living up to their name... then you will understand how these animals earned their spot on Nature's Most Wanted.

programme.title: The Incredible Dr. Pol S5E1
programme.desc: Summer is in full swing in central Michigan and Pol Vet Services has revved up to meet the growing needs of their clients - from farm calls to clinic emergencies, Dr. Pol and crew are full speed ahead. But animals are not the only ones in need of Dr. Pol's attention, as he and Charles embark on a mission to fix up his vintage DMC DeLorean for the local car show. The car will have to wait though, as the Pol duo have the pedal to the metal en route to a serious emergency - Bow Tie, a beloved family cow has suffered an enormous prolapse after giving birth. The longer the uterus is out the more it swells, so time is of the essence if they are to save Bow Tie in this emergency farm call. While Dr. Pol and Charles have their hands full, Dr. Brenda is headed to Caryl Dairy where the situation is grim for a cow struggling to give birth. With zero progress made since Dr. Brenda's arrival, the focus shifts from delivering the calf to saving the mother. Dr. Brenda resorts to a last ditc.

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S4E5

programme.title: Wild Sri Lanka E1
programme.desc: The seas surrounding Sri Lanka boasts an incredible array of habitats, all full of life. Sri Lanka's seas tell us much about how the island came to be – the vast, slow forces that underpin the extraordinary diversity of the island we see today. They also tell the story of Sri Lanka's complex climate and the ancient roots of many of the species that inhabit the island today.

Love Now
programme.desc: Hubungan yang saling berkaitan di antara dua pasang kekasih terjalin. Bagaimanakah mereka menjalani dan memperbaiki hubungan nan berbahaya dan rahasia ini?

programme.title: Love, Lies
programme.desc: Seorang wanita penghibur diliputi kecemburuan setelah temannya sukses menjadi penyanyi pop dan kekasihnya jatuh hati padanya. Merasa dikhianati, ia mencoba mendapatkan kembali hal-hal yang hilang darinya.

programme.title: Shoot Me In The Heart
programme.desc: Dua pemuda bertemu di sebuah rumah sakit jiwa. Soo-myung mengalami trauma karena sang ibu bunuh diri dan Seung-min dimasukkan secara paksa ke sana meskipun ia waras. Bagaimanakah jalinan takdir mereka?

programme.title: The Battleship Island
programme.desc: Selama pemerintahan kolonial Jepang, sekitar 400 warga Korea diwajibkan untuk bekerja di Pulau Hashima. Ketika rahasia kelam pulau itu terungkap, para pekerja Korea berencana untuk melarikan diri.

programme.title: We Are Brothers
programme.desc: Dua kakak beradik yang terpisah sejak lahir bersatu kembali 30 tahun kemudian dan melakukan perjalanan untuk mencari ibu mereka yang menderita Alzheimer.

programme.title: The Mayor
programme.desc: Byeon Jong-gu, walikota Seoul, mencalonkan diri sebagai presiden. Ia menggunakan segala cara untuk menyembunyikan rahasia-rahasia tergelapnya dari publik yang menyukainya.

programme.title: Scarlet Innocence
programme.desc: Deokee, seorang gadis dari suatu kota kecil, dicampakkan oleh seorang dosen bernama Hak-kyu yang menjalin hubungan terlarang dengannya. Delapan tahun kemudian, ia membalas dendam usai sang dosen mengalami kebutaan.

programme.title: The Pirates
programme.desc: Tepat sebelum berdirinya Dinasti Joseon, para utusan dari Tiongkok kehilangan Segel Kerajaan karena seekor paus. Sekelompok bandit berusaha untuk mengambilnya demi hadiah besar dan bertemu dengan sekelompok perompak.

programme.title: I Am The King
programme.desc: Seorang pangeran yang melarikan diri bertemu dengan seorang budak yang sangat mirip dengan dirinya. Sang pangeran disangka sebagai budak dan si budak dinobatkan sebagai Raja.

programme.title: Coffee Mate
programme.desc: Seorang ibu rumah tangga bertemu dengan seorang tukang kayu di sebuah kafe. Mereka menjadi 'rekan minum kopi' tanpa niat apapun hanya sekedar bertemu di kafe. Kemudian, mereka saling jatuh cinta.

programme.title: Blood And Ties
programme.desc: Seorang jurnalis mencurigai ayahnya adalah seorang penculik kejam yang melarikan diri 15 tahun yang lalu.

programme.title: Detective K: The Living Dead
programme.desc: Detektif K dan rekannya dibantu seorang wanita penderita amnesia guna menguak suatu kasus pembunuhan. Mereka melihat gigitan vampir pada jasad para korban dan menyadari bahwa wanita itu terkait dengan kematian mereka.

programme.title: The Outlaws
programme.desc: Untuk menjaga perdamaian, seorang detektif nan kejam dan timnya berencana untuk meringkus gangster yang paling ditakuti di Seoul.

programme.title: Rules Of Dating
programme.desc: Seorang wanita nan sinis bekerja sebagai guru di sebuah sekolah. Saat sang guru pengawas mendekatinya, pertempuran antara hati dan logika dimulai karena keduanya ragu dengan perasaan masing-masing.

programme.title: Thread Of Lies
programme.desc: Terpukul akibat bunuh diri sang putri yang berusia 14 tahun, seorang ibu dan putri tertuanya bertekad untuk memecahkan misteri kematian putrinya itu dengan menyelami kehidupan gadis yang merundung sang putri.

programme.title: Hit-And-Run Squad
programme.desc: Seorang detektif polisi veteran dan seorang polisi muda bekerjasama untuk menangkap seorang pengusaha kaya raya sekaligus pembalap yang gila kecepatan dan kekuasaan.

programme.title: My Boss, My Teacher
programme.desc: Doo-sik adalah seorang mahasiswa senior di pagi hari dan bekerja di sebuah geng di malam hari. Namun, masalah muncul saat bosnya meminta ia bekerja untuknya di pagi hari, saat ia berada di kampus.

programme.title: Countdown
programme.desc: Seorang penagih utang menderita kanker hati dan harus mendapatkan transplantasi hati dalam sepuluh hari. Seorang penipu bersedia mendonorkan hatinya jika ia bisa melacak pria yang memasukkannya ke dalam penjara.
